parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Engine Control Module (ECM) Insulative Spray
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ECM insulative spray can cause erratic idle, misfiring, and electrical shorts, leading to stalling, loss of power, and potentially dangerous situations, such as sudden acceleration or deceleration.
The cooling system failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to stalling, engine damage, and potentially dangerous situations.
The electrical system failure can cause loss of rear tail lamps and dash lamps, leading to reduced visibility and potentially dangerous situations.
symptoms: Loss of rear tail lamps and dash lamps
brake turning and hazard lamps still working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or irregular idling can cause loss of control, accidents, or stranding, especially on highways or in heavy traffic.
Cracked exhaust manifolds can cause exhaust fumes to enter the cabin, potentially leading to fatal accidents.
symptoms: smell of exhaust fumes inside the vehicle
sheared pipe from manifold to converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause engine failure, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to fires.
Clutch and ECM issues can cause loss of control, accidents, or stranding, especially on highways or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
engine RPM increases during warm/hot weather
throttle must be physically moved to return to normal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket damage can cause engine failure, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to fires.
ECU and idle air control valve issues can cause engine stalling, irregular idling, and loss of control.
symptoms: new IAC/idle air control valve needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not properly protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy during an accident
airbags do not deploy despite meeting the deployment threshold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The over-aggressive deployment of airbags can cause serious injuries or fatalities, as the force of the deployment can be excessive.
symptoms: Airbags deploy with too much force

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy or deploy incorrectly, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: airbag replaced with one from another vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to inflate properly can reduce their effectiveness in protecting vehicle occupants, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags deploy but do not inflate
airbags do not deploy due to inflation failure.
